Kim Jong Il sends autograph to ministry officials
 &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, February 19 (KCNA) - General Secretary Kim Jong Il sent the following autograph to the officials of the Ministry of Construction and Building-Materials Industries in reply to their letter:&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   "Let us vigorously advance. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
                      February 10, 1999&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
                      Kim Jong Il."&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The officials said in their letter that Kim Jong Il visited the Thaechon General Hydro-Electric Power Plant on the first leg of his guidance to economic sector this year following last year and indicated in detail the orientation and ways of building large-scale hydro-electric power plants on an extensive scale to solve the electricity problem of the country and revitalize the independent national economy.
   They, in charge of the building of large-scale hydro-electric power plants, vowed to tap locally available reserves and complete the underground coal gasification power plant, the first of its kind in Korea, the Namgang Power Plant, the remaining project of the Thaechon General Hydro-Electric Power Plant and the second-stage construction of the Anbyon Youth Power Plant, they said.

Japan will be held responsible
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, February 19 (KCNA) -- The Japanese Foreign Minister in separate meetings with the present chief executive of South Korea and senior officials of the military in Seoul said both sides should adopt "countermeasures" to cope with "missile threat" from the North Korea.
   Rodong Sinmun today describes his remarks as a provocation and challenge to the north.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Lurking Behindit is a sinister intention, the news analyst observes, adding:   The Japanese reactionaries are crying for strengthened "cooperation system" and "countermeasures" on the plea of non-existent "missile threat" from the north, spreading the rumours about a "crisis." They seek to divert attention of the international community from their criminal scheming to become a military power and realise overseas expansion. They also seek to strain the situation, block inter-Korean dialogue and economic cooperation which were proposed at a joint meeting of the government, political parties and organisations of the DPRK, encourage the South Korean authorities to step up confrontation with the north for a fratricidal war and, furthermore, prevent Korea from being reunified.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   If they dare take military actions against the DPRK, persisting in their smear campaign against it, the Korean people will crush them without mercy.
   We have numerous things to square with Japan. If Japan chooses a battlefield as a place to settle accounts, we will annihilate them with force.

Songs in praise of great man
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, February 19 (KCNA) -- New songs were recently created in Korea.   Rodong Sinmun introduced over 10 songs this year.   Korean radio and television are broadcasting songs created by many art organizations including the merited choir of the Korean People's Army, the Pochonbo Electronic Music Band and the Mansudae Art Troupe.   The new songs include "Let us sing of dear commander of people", "Cradle of happiness" and "Oh, night on Jong Il Peak" and other songs in praise of General Secretary Kim Jong Il.   The songs reflect ardent reverence for Kim Jong Il who has made tireless efforts for the prosperity of the country and happiness of the people.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Korean musicians and composers produced a lot of songs in praise of him, carrying the people's mind and desire.    Last year they created tens of songs including "He is our dear father" and "Let us be a satellite of sun."   Immortal revolutionary song "Song of General Kim Jong Il", created in Juche 86 (1997), is being sung as a doxology of the era and the great man among not only the Korean people but the progressive people of the world as well.   "Collection of 2,000 Korean songs" which was created between 1974 and 1993 and many other collections of songs contain such songs of praising him as "Let's support our supreme commander with arms" and "Dear name."&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Progressive artists of the world have created songs in praise of the greatness of Kim Jong Il.   Recently, they created "Guiding star of Korea" (Ukraine), "Anyone, please meet him" (Syria), "Eternal Sun" (Nigeria) and many other songs.   Particularly, foreign artists sang many songs written and composed by themselves in praise of Kim Jong Il, at the April Spring Friendship Art Festival which was held every year from Juche 71 (1982).

Collusion with Japanese reactionaries
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, February 19 (KCNA) -- The South Korean chief executive in a "personal message" handed by Pak Thae Jun, president of the "United Liberal Democrats", on a visit to Japan to the Japanese Prime Minister on Feb. 17 said that "Japan's cooperation is needed more than ever before" in carrying into practice South Korea's "engagement policy", the policy designed to disintegrate and stifle the DPRK, according to a foreign news report.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The "engagement policy toward the north" on the lips of the present chief executive of South Korea is a policy of confrontation with the north, which is fully contradictory to the idea of the three principles of national reunification.   He paved the way for intensifying collusion with the Japanese militarist forces of aggression in the anti-north moves during his Japan trip last October and the Seoul tour of the director general of the Japan Defence Agency last January.  Not content with this, he asked for Japan's "cooperation" again.   Such criminal act fully reveals his dirty traitorous nature.

"Evening of Japan, India and Korea" held
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, February 19 (KCNA) -- An "Evening of Japan, India and Korea" was sponsored by the National Liaison Council of Japan Societies for the Study of Works of Kim Jong Il in Osaka, on Feb. 9 on the occasion of the 57th birthday of General Secretary Kim Jong Il.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Present were Mekumi Tada, representative of the council, and other Japanese personages of all social standings.    A delegation of the Korean Social Scientists Society, a delegation of India led by Vishwanath, secretary general of the Juche Idea Study Society of India and secretary general of the "International Kim Il Sung Prize" Council, and O Su Jin, chairman of the Osaka prefectural headquarters of Chongryon (General Association of Korean Residents in Japan), were present on invitation.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Speeches were made and lectures on the subjects "Korea advances under banner of independence" and "Friendship with Korea in India" were given.   Japanese personages declared that they would loudly call for rectifying the Japanese government's hostile policy toward the DPRK and continue conducting energetic activities  for early normalization of Japan-DPRK diplomatic relations.   A letter to Kim Jong Il was adopted at the function.

25 years of Kim Jong Il's work observed
 &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, February 19 (KCNA) -- General Secretary Kim Jong Il at a national training course for party propagandists on February 19, 1974, set out some immediate tasks of party ideological work for modeling the whole society on the Juche idea.   Rodong Sinmun today runs an editorial captioned "Let us accomplish cause of modeling whole society on Juche idea under guidance of party" to mark the day.   In the work he formulated the revolutionary idea of the President Kim Il Sung for the first time in history and declared the modeling of the whole society on the Juche idea maximum programme of the Workers' Party of Korea (WPK).&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The work has proved its worth in effecting great upswing in the Korean revolution for the past 25 years, the editorial says, and goes on:   The history of the Korean revolution that has made triumphant progress under the banner of the modeling of the whole society on the Juche idea witnessed the growth of a huge army of revolutionaries of Juche type and signal creation and miracles in socialist construction.   The WPK is great in that it has carried out the remolding of all the members of society as genuine revolutionaries of Juche type with credit.   The Korean people prove to be fighters to protect the leader devotedly and absolute followers, resolute defenders and thorough implementers of his ideology.  Kim Jong Il has performed undying exploits in the accomplishment of historic cause of transforming the economy and culture as demanded by the Juche idea.   He has always adhered to the principle of weathering stern trials through a bold attack and of foiling the enemy's economic blockade with a strategy of self-reliance in socialist construction.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   A historic task to carry forward the cause of socialism and bring it to completion has been carried out with credit for the last 25 years.   The efforts made to model the whole society on the Juche idea laid solid organizational and ideological foundations to carry through his ideas and fully ensure his guidance and made the authority of his leadership unquestioned.   All politico-ideological and material foundations have been laid for pure inheritance of the lineage of Juche  and the building of Korea into a powerful socialist nation resplendent for the august name of Kim Il Sung. That is a proud summing-up of the 25-year-long history.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The editorial calls for sustained progress under the uplifted banner of the modeling of the whole society on the Juche idea.   It is necessary to firmly uphold the ideas of Kim Jong Il and thoroughly apply them in all aspects of the revolution and construction and strengthen in every way, the monolithic unity of the whole party, the whole army and the entire people around him, adds the editorial.
